  "interpretation": {
    "khinchin_theorem": "Khinchin's theorem states that for almost all real numbers, the geometric mean of CF partial quotients converges to K \u2248 2.685452. However, specific algebraic numbers (quadratic irrationals have periodic CFs) and many mathematically interesting constants may not satisfy this.",
    "expectation": "We expect most OEIS sequences to NOT be Khinchin-compliant, because OEIS sequences are curated for mathematical interest \u2014 they are not 'almost all' reals. Famous transcendental constants (pi, e, gamma) are conjectured to be Khinchin-compliant but this is unproven."
